2.00	Nosocomial_infections	Nosocomial infection	A nosocomial infection (nos-oh-koh-mi-al), also known as a hospital-acquired infection or HAI, is an infection whose development is favoured by a hospital environment, such as one acquired by a patient during a hospital visit or one developing among hospital staff. Such infections include fungal and bacterial infections and are aggravated by the reduced resistance of individual patients.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/34/Contaminated_surfaces_increase_cross-transmission.jpg/230px-Contaminated_surfaces_increase_cross-transmission.jpg
